cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) because it introduces a new text representation model that does not rely on symbolic units such as words or tokens. It may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) because the model is trained on a corpus and the paper discusses its performance on tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) because the model is a novel approach to representing text. Neural Networks (cs.NE) is another possible sub-category because the paper mentions using a neural network architecture. Finally, Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is a possible sub-category because the paper evaluates the model's performance on an information extraction task.
